<http://www.spektrix.com/thecultch/event/130601APHPQJHJPRKCMSLRCJTVSRDKMKQ> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Reading: Oriental Cowboy Moshpit";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">Garvin Chan</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Jim Green House Studio 1885 Venables St.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>In the Albertan Badlands there is a town with a pawn shop. In that pawn shop is a copy of Chinese family records thought to have been burned during the Cultural Revolution. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Now, it is up to a Chinese cowboy to retrieve those records in time to present them as part of their father’s funeral in this absurd, wacky, and strangely heartfelt heist play.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>This is Oriental Cowboy Mosh Pit. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Yeehaw. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>All <span class=\"BoldText\">rEvolver Festival readings</span> are by donation and <span class=\"BoldText\">100% of all donations go directly to the artists. </span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Donations start at a minimum of $5 (which comes to just under $9 after ticketing fees) and range up to $30. If you have more to give and would like to increase your donation, there is an option to do so at the checkout window.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Please note: readings cannot be booked with your festival pass.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Thank you for supporting emerging artists!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Audience Advisory</span>: Themes of violence, alcohol use<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Talkback</span>: May 31<span><br/></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-05-31T14:15:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
